<h4 id="telephone-bill">telephone bill</h4>
<p>請求(せいきゅう)明細(めいさい) means telephone bill. <br />
Why don’t they say the bill you should pay, instead of, they say the fee we ask.
Because, because, you need to think this in a japanese way, the second way is
more polite. It means the company request you, just more polite.
請求書(せいきゅうしょ): bill</p>

<h4 id="japanese-polite">Japanese Polite</h4>
<p>もう少し安くなりませんか。<br />
もう少し安くしてくしてくれませんか。<br /></p>
<ol>
  <li>use receive or give to show polite</li>
  <li>use negative to show polite</li>
</ol>

